President George W. Bush faced hostility during his farewell visit to Iraq when a journalist threw shoes at him, symbolizing the lingering resentment towards the Iraq war.
Despite the incident, Bush defended the invasion and emphasized the ongoing work needed for success.
The shoe-throwing incident highlighted the complex legacy of Bush's presidency, marked by the overthrow of Saddam Hussein but also marred by the violence and instability that followed.
The event underscored the deep divisions and mixed feelings among Iraqis towards the US presence and policies in their country.
